  },
  {
    question: 'What margin math should we use?',
    answer: 'At $263 AOV and 45% gross margin, full-price recovery yields $118.35. A 17% cart discount yields ~$98.23 — $20.12 gap per recovery when 40% would have returned without incentive.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which metrics matter?',
    answer: 'Margin per email order, Trend drop sell-through, Personalization completion rate, Discount dependency ratio.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should we discount abandoned carts?',
    answer: 'Proof and assistance first; discount only when contribution floor allows and segment shows discount sensitivity.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Email or SMS for this vertical?',
    answer: 'Email carries education and proof; SMS for time-bound inventory or shipping cutoff — always opt-in with caps.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do inventory issues affect recovery?',
    answer: 'Suppress OOS variants; route to back-in-stock. False urgency destroys trust in considered categories.',
  },
];
